MINGW64:/e/Tech/Haskell
/e/Tech/Haskell
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$haskell-wiki
echo
Haskell is a functional programming language that is designed
to be purely functional, which means that it treats computation
as the evaluation of mathematical functions and avoids side
effects as much as possible. Haskell is named after the
logician Haskell Curry, and it was first released in 1990.
Haskell is commonly used in academia for teaching functional
programming concepts, but it is also used in industry for a
variety of applications, including financial modeling, data
analysis, and web development. One of the key advantages of
Haskell is that it has a strong type system, which can catch
many errors at compile time and ensure that programs are
correct and reliable. Haskell also has a rich ecosystem of
libraries and tools, including the Cabal package manager and
the Stack build tool. Haskell has a vibrant open-source
community that is constantly contributing new libraries and
tools to the language.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/HTML
/e/Tech/HTML
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$html-wiki
echo
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is a standard markup
language used for creating web pages and web applications. It
provides a set of tags that are used to structure the content of
a web page and describe how it should be displayed in a web
browser. HTML provides a way to create text, images, videos,
forms, and other types of media on a web page and define how
they should be arranged. HTML is used because it is the
fundamental building block of the web. It provides the structure
and content for every website and web application. With HTML,
you can create a website from scratch or modify an existing
website to meet your specific needs. HTML is a language that
is easy to learn and widely supported by web browsers and web
development tools. HTML is an essential part of web
development and a valuable tool to learn for anyone who wants
to create a website or web application.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Node
/e/Tech/Node
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
NodeJS is an open-source, cross-platform JavaScript runtime
environment that allows developers to run JavaScript code
outside of a web browser. It is built on the V8 JavaScript
engine, the same engine that powers Google Chrome, and
provides an event-driven, non-blocking I/O model that makes it
suitable for building scalable and high-performance
applications. NodeJS is often used for building server-side
applications and APIs, as well as for building command-line
tools and scripts. It is particularly popular for building web
applications with real-time features, such as chat applications
and online games. NodeJS also has a large and vibrant
ecosystem of third-party libraries and frameworks, which make
it easier to build complex applications quickly and efficiently.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/PostgreSQL
/e/Tech/PostgreSQL
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
echo
PostgreSQL, also known as Postgres, is an open-source
relational database management system (RDBMS) that is
widely used for storing, retrieving, and managing structured
data. It is known for its reliability, scalability, and extensibility,
and is often used in mission-critical applications.
PostgreSQL is based on the SQL language, but it has several
advanced features that set it apart from other relational
database management systems. For example, it supports
complex data types, such as arrays and JSON, and has built-in
support for full-text search, spatial data, and XML.
PostgreSQL is often used in web applications, particularly in
data-driven applications that require a high degree of scalability
and reliability. It can handle large amounts of data and can be
easily scaled to handle high traffic volumes. Additionally,
because it is open-source, it is free to use and can be
customized to fit the specific needs of an application.
postgreSQL
MINGW64:/e/Tech/jQuery
/e/Tech/jQuery
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$jquery
echo
jQuery is a fast, small, and feature-rich JavaScript library that
simplifies web development. It provides a variety of utilities that
make it easier to manipulate HTML documents, handle events,
create animations, and make AJAX requests to the server.
jQuery is cross-platform and compatible with all modern web
browsers. jQuery is commonly used in front-end web
development for creating dynamic and interactive user
interfaces. It is often used to create animations, add visual
effects, and enhance user experience. jQuery is also used for
client-side form validation and handling form submissions, as
well as for making AJAX requests to the server to fetch or
submit data without requiring a page reload. Overall, jQuery is a
versatile tool that simplifies web development and enhances
the functionality of web applications.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Python
/e/Tech/Python
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$python-wiki
echo
Python is a high-level programming language that is
interpreted, object-oriented, and dynamically typed. It was first
released in 1991 and has since become one of the most
popular programming languages in use today. Python is known
for its simple syntax, ease of learning, and large standard
library, which makes it a versatile language used in a wide
range of applications. Python is commonly used in many fields
including web development, scientific computing, data analysis,
artificial intelligence and machine learning, automation, and
game development. It is a popular choice for building web
applications and backend systems, often in conjunction with
web frameworks like Django or Flask. In the scientific
computing and data analysis fields, Python is often used for
processing and analyzing large datasets, as well as for building
visualizations.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Processing
/e/Tech/Processing
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$processing
echo
Processing is an open-source programming language and
development environment based on Java that is designed for
visual artists, designers, and creative coders. Processing
provides a simplified and user-friendly interface for creating
graphics and interactive applications, making it an accessible
tool for those who may not have a background in programming.
Processing was created with the goal of making it easy to
create visual and interactive applications by abstracting away
many of the complex details of programming. It provides a set
of built-in functions and libraries for creating 2D and 3D
graphics, animations, and interactive applications, as well as
support for various input devices such as keyboards, mice, and
cameras.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Sass
/e/Tech/Sass
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$sass
echo
Sass (short for Syntactically Awesome Style Sheets) is a
preprocessor scripting language that is interpreted or compiled
into Cascading Style Sheets (CSS). It adds a layer of
functionality and abstraction to CSS, making it easier and more
efficient to write and manage complex stylesheets. Sass
provides features such as variables, nested rules, functions,
and mixins, which allow for more organized and modular code.
One of the key benefits of Sass is its ability to simplify the
process of creating responsive web designs. With features like
media queries and variables, developers can create more
flexible and adaptable layouts with less code. Sass also
provides a way to reuse code across multiple stylesheets using
mixins, which can reduce redundancy and increase
maintainability.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/MongoDB
/e/Tech/MongoDB
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$mongodb
echo
MongoDB is a popular open-source document-oriented NoSQL
database that stores data in flexible, JSON-like documents. It
was developed in 2007 by MongoDB Inc. and is currently
maintained by a community of developers. MongoDB uses a
document model to store data, which means that data is
organized into collections of documents rather than tables with
rows and columns, as in a relational database. Each document
is a BSON object that can be queried and indexed for fast
retrieval. One of the primary benefits of MongoDB is its ability
to handle large volumes of unstructured or semi-structured
data. It provides high availability and automatic scaling, making
it suitable for large-scale and high-traffic applications. It also
offers a rich set of features, including ad hoc queries, indexing,
and aggregation, as well as built-in support for geospatial data
and full-text search.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Bash
/e/Tech/Bash
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$bash
echo
Bash is a Unix shell and command language, which is the
default shell for most Linux and macOS operating systems. It
stands for (Bourne-Again SHell) named after its predecessor,
the Bourne shell (sh). Bash is a command-line interface (CLI)
that allows users to interact with the operating system by
entering commands and receiving output. Bash allows users to
navigate and manipulate files and directories, run programs,
automate tasks using shell scripts, and perform other common
computing tasks. It provides a number of built-in commands
and utilities, as well as the ability to create and use custom
commands and scripts. Bash also supports features such as
command history, tab completion, and environment variables,
which allow users to customize their shell experience.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Linux
/e/Tech/Linux
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$linux
echo
Linux is a free and open-source operating system based on the
Unix-like operating systems, which was first released in 1991. It
was created by Linus Torvalds and has since grown to become
one of the most popular operating systems in the world,
powering servers, supercomputers, and mobile devices. Linux
is known for its stability, security, and flexibility, and is widely
used by developers, system administrators, and other tech-
savvy users. One of the key advantages of Linux is its open-
source nature, which allows developers and users to access the
source code, modify it, and distribute their own versions of the
operating system. This has led to a vast ecosystem of free and
open-source software built around Linux, with many powerful
tools and applications available for a wide range of purposes.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Plutus
/e/Tech/Plutus
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$plutus
echo
Plutus is a programming platform specifically designed for
writing smart contracts on the Cardano blockchain. It is an
open-source platform that leverages Haskell, a purely
functional programming language, for developing smart
contracts. Developers can use Plutus to create custom smart
contracts that run on the Cardano blockchain. Plutus provides
developers with a suite of tools and libraries for creating smart
contracts, including a simulator for testing and debugging, an
online editor for developing and deploying contracts, and a
command-line interface for interacting with the blockchain.
Additionally, Plutus uses the Cardano Settlement Layer (CSL) to
provide a secure and scalable blockchain platform for smart
contract deployment.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Bootstrap
/e/Tech/Bootstrap
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$bootstrap
echo
Bootstrap is a free and open-source CSS framework that is
widely used by developers to create responsive and mobile-first
web pages. It was developed by Twitter and has since become
one of the most popular CSS frameworks available. With its
extensive library of pre-built components, it makes web design
a breeze. Bootstrap has an active community, with plenty of
resources available, including documentation, templates, and
code snippets you can leverage to design a clean application
relatively quickly. With all these features, Bootstrap is definitely
a tool that any developer should have in their toolkit.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Solidity
/e/Tech/Solidity
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$solidity
echo
Solidity is a high-level programming language used to write
smart contracts on the Ethereum blockchain. It was developed
by the Ethereum Foundation and is used to build decentralized
applications (DApps) on the blockchain. Solidity has a similar
syntax to JavaScript and is designed to be both easy to learn
and secure. Smart contracts are self-executing contracts with
the terms of the agreement directly written into code. They
allow for decentralized transactions, eliminating the need for a
middleman or third party. Solidity is the most popular language
for developing smart contracts and is widely used in the
Ethereum ecosystem. It is compiled into bytecode that can be
executed on the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM). A number of
other blockchains have decided to add EVM support to enable
developers to work create applications for their platform.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/CSS
/e/Tech/CSS
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$css
echo
As a web developer, I use CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) every
day to style and design web pages. CSS is a style sheet
language used to describe the presentation of an HTML
document. CSS is essential for creating visually appealing and
engaging websites. One of the most powerful features of CSS
is its ability to cascade, or inherit, styles across multiple
elements on a web page. Meaning that you can define a style
for a parent element and have it automatically applied to all of
its child elements, saving time and improving consistency
across your design. It is also leveraged to create responsive
designs that adapt to different screen sizes and resolutions, to
ensure that my pages look great on different browsers and
devices. CSS provides a range of options for creating web
applications, from a simple responsive design to creating
complex and unique features that bring your design to a new
level.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/React
/e/Tech/React
MINGW64
theforthlion@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$react
echo
As a web developer, I often use React, a popular open-source
JavaScript library developed by Facebook for building web
application user interfaces (UI). React enables developers to
create high-performance and reusable UI components using a
component-based architecture. These components are a
powerful tool for web development as they allow you to
combine HTML and JS in one component. Along with the ability
to fetch data, they offer a great way to create robust and
complex UI for any use case. I find React to be extremely useful
as it speeds up development and creates an environment
where you never code for just one project. With React Native,
you can also easily deploy your web application as a mobile
application on iOS or Android. React, along with other
frameworks, have truly reshaped the way we write web
applications.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Js
/e/Tech/Js
MINGW64
everettthefourth@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$javascript
echo
At its core JavaScript is a dynamic and versatile programming
language that has become the go-to language for both front-
end and back-end web development. It is popular for its ease of
use, platform compatibility, and the ability to create dynamic
and interactive web pages and applications. JavaScript has a
vast ecosystem with a growing number of front-end
frameworks and an ever-expanding amount of Node packages.
As a result, JavaScript has become my most used
programming language. Ive leveraged it when building a variety
of projects including writing web apps, web based games,
scripts to automate tasks, web scraping, and much more. The
famous quote by Jeff Atwood, Any application that can be
written in JavaScript, will eventually be written in JavaScript, is
a testament to the ubiquity of the language.
MINGW64:/e/Tech/Java
/e/Tech/Java
MINGW64
everettthefourth@DESKTOP-3MT17I6
$java
echo
The Java programming language is an excellent language to
work with. It is high-level and object-oriented, meaning that it is
designed to be easy to use and understand. The language is
designed to minimize implementation dependencies, which
makes it versatile and enables developers to write code once
and run it anywhere. This feature alone can save a lot of time
and effort, especially when developing large and complex
applications. Personally, Java holds a special place in my heart
as it was the first programming language I learned. I was
introduced to the fundamentals of programming through Java
in a software technology class in high school. The language
was intuitive and easy to pick up, which made it an ideal choice
for beginning. I also enjoyed working with Processing, a
graphical library built on top of Java. This library made it easy
to create visually rich and interactive applications.
